OL,3,CJersey's Chief Minister looks to delay
OL,4,Ckey living wage pledge
OL,6,FSpeaking to ITV News at a Chamber of
OL,7,FCommerce lunch, Deputy Farnham
OL,8,Fexplained: "I'm discussing this with
OL,9,Fthe Social Security and Economic
OL,10,FDevelopment Ministers because
OL,11,Fintroducing increases to payroll in
OL,12,FJanuary will be much harder for
OL,13,Fbusinesses in the quieter months of
OL,14,Fthe year, so I'm hoping we can push
OL,15,Fthat to April.
OL,17,F"I would like step one from 1 April
OL,18,F2025 and step two from 1 April 2026,
OL,19,Fjust to help businesses."
