OL,3,CJersey's Chief Minister looks to delay
OL,4,Ckey living wage pledge
OL,6,FEmployers currently have to pay staff
OL,7,Fa minimum salary of #11.64 an hour,
OL,8,Frather than the living wage of #13.41
OL,9,Fwhich is set by the charity Caritas
OL,10,FJersey under licence from the UK's
OL,11,FLiving Wage Foundation.
OL,13,FReacting to Deputy Farnham's comments,
OL,14,Fthe organisation posted on X, formerly
OL,15,FTwitter: "Very disappointed ...
OL,16,FPushing back next MW (minimum wage)
OL,17,Fincrease to April means those in
OL,18,Fpoverty/low wages are not helped at
OL,19,Fmost difficult time of year! Business
OL,20,Fprioritised over people. Poor!"
